This paper deals with privacy concerns related to the transmission of location information on the web, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a privacy framework for the consideration of location information, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI). The analysis of the W3C Geolocation API involves evaluating the specification and its use in the wild, which could be categorized under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper recommends modifications to the API, which could involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) considerations.
